net.adamcin.oakpal.core

Class ScriptProgressCheck

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.adamcin.oakpal.core.ScriptProgressCheck
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProgressCheck, ScanListener, ViolationReporter

    @ProviderType
public final class ScriptProgressCheck
extends Object
implements ProgressCheck
    The ScriptProgressCheck uses the Invocable interface from JSR223 to listen for scan events and optionally report check violations.

    You may implement only the methods you need to enforce your package check rules.

    getCheckName()
    ProgressCheck.getCheckName()
    startedScan()

    ProgressCheck.beforeExtract(PackageId, Session, PackageProperties, MetaInf, List)
    importedPath(packageId, path, node)
    ProgressCheck.importedPath(PackageId, String, Node)
    deletedPath(packageId, path, inspectSession)
    ProgressCheck.deletedPath(PackageId, String, Session)
    afterExtract(packageId, inspectSession)
    ProgressCheck.afterExtract(PackageId, Session)
    finishedScan()
    ScanListener.finishedScan()

    To report package violations, a ScriptProgressCheck.ScriptHelper is bound to the global variable "oakpal".
